<h1>Problem 944 - 2021 Taiwan IMOC, G9, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let the incenter and the \(A\)-excenter of \(\triangle ABC\) be \(I\) and \(I_A\), respectively. Let \(BI\) intersect \(AC\) at \(E\) and \(CI\) intersect \(AB\) at \(F\). Suppose that the reflections of \(I\) with respect to \(EF, FI_A, EI_A\) are \(X, Y, Z\) respectively. Show that \(\odot (XYZ)\) and \(\odot (ABC)\) are tangent to each other.</p>
